track_notes: Guajalote Peak is a short climb that is less than a mile and around 500 feet. There is no trail, but its pretty easy bushwhacking. The approach road is 3.7 miles and probably only for real off road 4WD vehicles. Im glad I didnt take my Ford F150 in there. Its pretty rough. Instead, I rode my mountain bike on the approach and then climbed the peak on foot. There were a few tough hills going in, but the ride out was fast and easy. I uploaded a separate track for the approach road.

This is the 3.7 mile approach road that takes you to the base of the peak. You can hike it or ride it on a mountain bike. If you want to drive it, make sure you have a high clearance 4WD off road vehicle. The road if very rough and narrow with lots of sharp rocks. I could have got my F150 in there but I would have beaten the hell out of it and scratched it up good.
track_title: Guajalote Approach Road - 4WD Off Road Only

track_notes: This road is good for an SUV/Truck. Some rocky areas but not bad. You can find parking areas past where I parked.
